name: MacKay building
directions: Upstairs, first floor (lift is available), turn left out of the lift or tern left at the top of the stairs, through the door and left along the corridor. The toilet is the third door on the right.

name: Simply Done Donuts
directions: In the back to your left, there is also a sign that directs you to it, though it is in cursive and kind of in the dark so it can be hard to read. There is a changing table but there is only one toliet. Single stall with a door that locks. The sink is also in the bathroom. Sometimes you have to let the workers know if they are out of paper towels, tissue paper or soap. They are open Tuesday-Friday, 7 am-2pm and Friday-Sunday, 8 am-4 pm
comment: You do not have to be a paying customer and there is no key to get back there.  As long as you are being respectful and don't trash the bathroom, you should be fine. Though I would recommend to just ask to use the bathroom first, just so the manager doesn't get worried you are trying to hide drugs in the bathroom or steal (this has apparently happened before).

name: MNSU Armstrong Hall
directions: Near the College of Education area of Armstrong. You can literally enter via any entrance of armstrong and just keep walking on the first floor once you’re in the building and it’s next to a stairway and an exit (it’s near the College of Education). There is an elevator right next to the bathroom and they are both ada compliant.
comment: MNSU is LGBT friendly and they are fairly friendly for people with disabilities. The disabilities office is in the basement of the library (which is not the best spot but it works).

name: MNSU Memorial Library
directions: It is on the first floor near the Government documents section and vending machines. It is also by the other restrooms and drinking fountains.
comment: You don’t need a college id to enter. It is ADA approved. Just a heads up the sink has high water pressure so that’s fun. The bathroom is fairly clean as well.

name: Mom and Pop’s
comment: You don’t have to be a “paying customer”. The bathroom is ADA friendly and accessible. The patio entrance has one small curb off the road but other than that the concrete is smooth and such. The bathroom is in a hallway that is a little narrow but it is wheelchair accessible. The bathrooms are clean and there are two of them. All of the staff are also extremely kind and this place is LGBT+ friendly and friendly to people with disabilities!

name: Mom and Pop’s Ice Cream Shop
comment: You can walk in and use the bathroom even without being a “paying customer”. There is an accessible entrance via the patio entrance with one small curb. The bathrooms are gender neutral and they are a safe space. The restrooms are also clean.

name: Woolworths toilet

name: Zimmerman Basement Universal
directions: Take elevator to basement and then follow sign for "oversized periodicals" towards the north. When you reach the north wall, turn right and then turn right again at the door to the custodian's office. Bathroom will be on your left. Note that the described route will not be accessable to wider wheelchairs, alternative routes almost always exist though but will vary depending on the position of the bookshelves
comment: Must show UNM student or government issued ID to access Zimmerman Library
